	   <tr><td colspan=2>I never bothered with the focus items until level 34 at which time I was able to kill the giants I needed to kill in order to get the toes and components. If you feel the focus items are needed, it shouldn't be too hard to get them by auctioning for them, or just asking a high level mage if he has any extras. The Hill Giant named Gornit in the OOT yields all of the toes (sometimes multiple toes from a single kill), should be able to get them from who ever is camping him.<br>The gems were the biggest obstacle, since they cost so much. Anyway, hope this helps, I had to go kill gators in Cazic Thule to get my shovel, think I got the stein in Najena, but there are help files that tell you where all the components are dropped.  Good luck<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
