	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I am level 13 and I am wearing a Robe of the Oracle.  I have a Stein of Moggok and a Spirit Tome.  For the equipment that you can't see, I have 2 X +3int earrings and 2 X +2int rings and some bracer that gives me some mana and hp I think and a Robe that gives me some nice AC and some cool saves to my Cold.  I also have a Savant's Cap, and a Turquoise Eyepatch and also a Bi medalian.  The rest is cloth I believe.  <br><br>Now some people might say that I am twinked, but I am NOT!!!  I bought all of these items with my own hard earned cash.  <br><br>To do this wait until you are level 5 and then get a friend to take you to Karnor Castle, or just get a port from a wizzie or a druid and run to the castle.  Then sit in the castle near some nice 46+ player and ask if you can loot the odd mob.  They will let you.  Trust me!  This is my second character (first is a level 10 SK).  Most of the time you can grab at least 10 to 20pp and hour.  easy money for some newbies.  I got some nice items from KC too.  Got myself some Singing Steel Boots - traded for my Spirit Tome.  The group that killed the mob let me loot the corpse - not my fault they are dumb.  But seriously folks.  People that say they can earn money is a joke.  It all depends on the risk you wantto take.  Yeah I died, but i got a revive everytime.  Might take a couple of minutes, but after level 5 you lay dead for 24 hours real time.<br><br>Basically what I am trying to say is that every person can get any amount of money if they want the risk.  Try it and post what happens.<br><br>Some people might say I am twinked, but it is hard to twink someone who's only other character is a level 10 shadowknight.<br><br>Trust me folks.  You get the cash and you get to meet a lot of people who when see you start growing up will help you out all the time.  I have met a lot of 50+ players that are always giving me tell and asking me if i need some help or some extra pp for spells. <br><br>Well now that I said my piece I am going to go.<br><br>Thanks for listening (or reading I guess).<br><br>Nibzen<br>Magician of the 13th.<br>Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
