<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97181536613594></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97181536613594><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=97181536613594>What I have done (1-17)</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=97181536613594#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 17th 4:42 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've played many, many characters, and so far, I always come back to my Magician.  He's just a ton of fun to play.  Harder but funner then a Necro, in my opinion.  But anyway, here's an outline of what I did...<br><br>1-4:  Pretty basic.  Newbie stuff.  In Gfay, that is Bugs, dogs and little orcs, with some pixies mixed in.  I never went to lesser fay, but there might be something good to hunt there as well.  Just push through these levels, they are fast.<br><br>4-8.  Congrats, you have Meditate and your new spells!  Get all that you can, but at the top shoud be  1) Damage spell 2) Pets (Water -&gt; Earth -&gt;Air -&gt; Fire) 3) anything/everything else.  Once you hit 4th in Gfay, Orc Hill is very nice solo or group experience till 6th, when it starts to even off.  At 7th it's boring.  Dont underestimate yourself!  With a good pet you should be able to take most things under red, but be careful.  Grouping in Crushbone can see you to 8th quickly.  Turn in the CB belts for EXP or sell then for 1pp +/- in Gfay.<br><br>8-12:  New direct damage spells: Flame Bolt and Shock of Blades.  Be careful with Flame Bolt!  It needs Line of Sight and hills, trees or people can block the Bolt.  Shock of Blades is resisted much less often and is very reliable.  Also, you get Fire shield.  Good spell!  Use it, it helps lots.  Put it on your pet before tough battles.  (By the way, I have found the Water pet to be the most reliable pet.  (Experiment for yourself, or if you want my explaination, E-mail me at rob85@maine.rr.com.)  I stared at the Snake pit in Black Borrow.  Snakes give good solo EXP and loot, I stayed here till 9th, then I went to East Commons to fight Asps till 10th.  Use the water pet, it's immune to poison.  After that, I went back to Crushbone to fight Leggionairs (bad spelling) till 12th.<br><br>12-16:  New spells, but no new real DD spell.  Burnout is a MUST, keep it on the pet all the time.  the Area effect spells CAN be good, but they are not really integral.  I got all the pets, especially the *water* pet.  I started off here in the Ocean of Tears, on Sister Island (first stop for the boat from Freeport.)  The EXP here is nice, but the loot is NUTS (Purity belt 9/10 kills, Halbard 100% of the time and rarely words, runes, or some gems).  After 13th, I went to Lake Rathetear (Start in Qeynos, find maps to get through the Karanas at www.eqmaps.com).  In the bottom corner is a Monk NPC named Jonah on a 5 minute spawn.  Loot is low, but EXP is nice.  He hits hard and drops fast, use a pet that can tank and use the fire shield!  Fought him 'till 15th, and I can't recall how I got to 16th...  which is odd, it was only 2 levels ago...  sorry guys.<br><br>16+:  Congrats, you're as high as me now.  Boy, that went fast, didn't it?  Here I got my spells in OOT (Ocean of Tears), ask where the lady is. ("Where's the lady who sells magi spells?" would probably do)  There is an island here with Spectres on the top (STAY WAY AWAY!) and skeletons wandering around.  Kill them and Gargoyles will spawn.  They start off almost all red to you, and hit 38-42.  Don't let the big guys scare you, they are take-able.  16th pet, Burnout, Fire Shield, send pet and Nuke with the new DD spell as needed.  If they drop loot, it is 1 or 2 Gargoyle Eyes, which sell for 8pp+ depending on faction and CHA.  Nice EXP here.  If you were patient, I bet you could stay here till 20th and get a ton of money, but I'm not the patient, I'm gonna leave soon.<br><br>Well, thats pretty much what I've done!  I play on Karana, as Zemplokazo mostly.  Drop me a tell if you're online.  Best of luck to you.<br><br>Fare thee well<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
