	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thought i would just add on to this guide and bring you up to the 29th spell lvl!  So here it goes...<br> <br>20-24:  Ahh lots of nice spells.  You get a 146 dmg bolt nuke, a new pet heal, fire sheild, and other nice stuff.  Get your pets (earth is a MUST others are TOTALLY useless!  TRUST ME..save your cash.  It doesnt' matter how much you love your water pet it's time to ditch it!).  OK...now there's 2 ways to do this.  The hard way, which is doing what everyone else does and fighting in groups at various places around Norath.  Or the easy way, in Lesser Faydark.  There's some huts right by the SF zone.  Inside one is a gnome named Saben Tuscross (or something like that).  She goes from 20-22.  She's got very few HP's, but hits in the 40's and very fast so you MUST use the earth pet to keep her off ya.  Oh, and you have to pull her out with the lvl 16 spell.  Then just nuke 2-3 times, heal pet and med.  Make sure to FS your pet.  Just kill her till lvl 24...you can do it in a weekend easy.<br><br>24-34:  Get your new Nuke (and get used to it...nothing new till lvl 34), and your pets (you will want to reasearch the fire/water pet this time for sure).  Now head to SK and go to the Paw spires.  Find a group, or do what i did and partner with a Druid and kite the Tesh Mas gnolls!  Awesome EXP, frequient FS weapon drops, 1-5pp in coin.  Just do those till about 30, and then go inside paw till 34.  That's where I am at lvl 32 and loving it.<br><br>Have fun!<br>-Tiiden VandorGriffin,<br>32nd Magician on Rodcet Nife<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
