	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, I've 'ad the same problem.....I'm a bit of a packrat, so I quite often find m'self laden with....JUNK!  The first thing you need to do, m'boy, is to GET OUTTA STEAMFONT!!!  (That is, provided you're still an up-and-comer......scratch that, I've never found that area too appealin'.)  Make yer way to Butcherblock - in my 'umble opinion, the loot and the questin' is much better there.  I spent the better part of my first 10 seasons there.<br><br>Ah, but I digress.....what was the question?  Oh, yes, the junk....well, I know that the sprockets are used for some high-level tinkerin' - powered gloves and catapults, as well as mechanized lockpicks, to name a few items.  The micro-servers, well I believe they're part of a quest to make Trueshot bows in Kelethin.  Other than that, I'm afraid I don't know what else they're good for, other than slowin' me down, whilst I run from Griffons in the Commons.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
